{
  "texts": [
    "158 The process is then repeated iteratively, with different principles being applied to the model's responses in each iteration.",
    "159 This helps the model learn to consider a broad range of ethical considerations when generating its outputs.",
    "160 Finally, the model is fine-tuned using the revised responses, adjusting its parameters to better align with the constitutional principles to ensure that it has a basic understanding of what constitutes helpful and harmless responses.",
    "161 The second stage of the Constitutional AI training process involves reinforcement learning, which bears some similarities to the human feedback approach.",
    "However, instead of relying on human feedback, Constitutional AI uses an AI model to evaluate the generated responses."
  ]
}